\end{table}

\section{Controller Code}

The Pi Pico 2W runs production controller code with the following key features:

\begin{itemize}
\item 1 kHz PWM generation at 60\% duty cycle
\item Real-time safety monitoring (voltage, current, temperature)
\item Emergency shutdown with hardware safety relay
\item GPS-synchronized data logging
\item Statistical validation across multiple test runs
\end{itemize}

\section{Test Protocol}

\subsection{Validation Test Sequence}
\begin{enumerate}
\item Record baseline current with coil inactive
\item Activate 5-second PWM burst (1 kHz, 60\% duty cycle)
\item Monitor with TCP0030A probe → Rigol DS1054Z oscilloscope
\item Cross-validate with Arduino + ACS712 sensors
\item Measure spatial effects with laser distance meter
\item Repeat minimum 10 trials for statistical significance
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Expected Measurements}
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Primary}: 5-6\% current boost detection
\item \textbf{Temporal}: GPS timestamps for all data points
\item \textbf{Spatial}: 0.1-0.5 meter distance changes during activation
\item \textbf{Statistical}: <5\% measurement variance across trials
\end{itemize}

\section{Simulation Framework}

The included \texttt{hlrt\_lattice\_simulation.py} file provides computational validation with:

\begin{itemize}
\item Lattice field dynamics simulation
\item Electromagnetic boost predictions
\item Fractal dimension calculations
\item Metric perturbation modeling
\item Gravitational wave propagation analysis
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Key Simulation Outputs}
\begin{align}
\text{Lattice spacing: } \lambda &= 1.24 \times 10^{-13} \text{ m}\\
\text{Graviton energy: } E_{\text{graviton}} &= 9.99 \times 10^6 \text{ eV}\\
\text{Fractal dimension: } D_F &= 1.934\\
\text{Predicted EM boost: } &= 5.8\%\\
\text{Enhanced current: } I_{\text{enhanced}} &= 10.58 \text{ A}
\end{align}

\section{Safety Protocols}

\subsection{Hardware Safety}
\begin{itemize}
\item Maximum BCAP voltage: 5.4V (safe operating limit)
\item Current limiting: 20A maximum system current
\item Emergency stop with immediate PWM shutdown
\item Hardware safety relay for complete power cutoff
\item Thermal monitoring with automatic shutdown
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Operational Safety}
\begin{itemize}
\item 60-second cooldown between test runs
\item Continuous monitoring during all operations
\item GPS timing for precise test synchronization
\item Multiple independent measurement systems
\item Comprehensive data logging for analysis
\end{itemize}

